WEBVTT

01:50.632 --> 01:52.938
ELI: It's hard
to fend off the dark.

01:52.982 --> 01:55.724
Especially what hides
within it.

01:55.767 --> 01:58.814
I see it sometimes
out of the corner
of my eye.

01:58.857 --> 02:02.209
Hear its footsteps,
one behind mine.

02:02.252 --> 02:05.212
I feel it every time
I turn off the lights.

02:07.866 --> 02:10.826
My fear only
makes it stronger.

02:13.045 --> 02:14.612
I know what it is.

02:14.656 --> 02:16.527
It's evil.

02:16.571 --> 02:18.834
And the evil I know
has a name.

02:21.053 --> 02:22.620
The Burghly Monster.

02:23.230 --> 02:25.014
The Burglary what?

02:26.058 --> 02:27.669
The Burghly Monster.

02:27.712 --> 02:30.411
He collects kids' souls,
and he's after mine.

02:31.151 --> 02:32.587
If he gets my soul,

02:34.980 --> 02:36.939
then he might
come after one of you.

02:39.202 --> 02:41.465
So if I don't show up
for school one day,

02:41.509 --> 02:43.815
-you'll know that
the Burghly Monster got me.

02:45.382 --> 02:46.644
MISS PERRY: Yes, Hillary.

02:46.688 --> 02:48.690
I think I need
to go to the bathroom.

02:48.733 --> 02:50.735
-MISS PERRY: You may
be excused.

02:50.779 --> 02:54.348
Eli, put your drawings
on my desk.

02:58.047 --> 03:00.789
-GIRLS: You go first,
I go last.

03:00.832 --> 03:03.574
Tell my ears anything.

03:03.618 --> 03:06.490
-Unicorn.
-Puppy.

03:06.534 --> 03:08.840
-Cat.
-Dog.

03:20.548 --> 03:21.853
BOY: Hurry, I'm coming.

03:25.509 --> 03:26.510
Whoo-hoo!

03:36.694 --> 03:38.566
-Bug.
-Bat.

03:39.436 --> 03:41.569
-Marmot.
-Owl.

03:41.612 --> 03:45.877
CHILDREN:
Ashes, ashes,
we all fall down!

03:45.921 --> 03:49.185
Hey, Eli, what the hell
were you thinking?

03:49.229 --> 03:52.710
Emily said that if I warned
everybody about
the Burghly Monster,

03:52.754 --> 03:55.757
he might leave me alone
and go after someone else.

03:55.800 --> 03:58.020
Dude, it was
show and tell.

03:58.063 --> 03:59.500
It doesn't have to
be so heavy.

03:59.543 --> 04:02.067
Emily is clearly
making it up.

04:02.111 --> 04:03.243
Just think about it.

04:03.286 --> 04:05.201
The Burghly Monster.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.247
That's a super lame name
for a monster.

04:07.595 --> 04:08.639
Come on.

04:08.683 --> 04:10.206
ELI: Sam, the name's
not important.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.642
I felt him.

04:11.686 --> 04:12.948
He hides
behind the furnace

04:12.991 --> 04:14.863
and uses the vents
to get around the house.

04:15.385 --> 04:16.430
He watches me.

04:16.473 --> 04:17.953
I think he's after my soul.

04:17.996 --> 04:19.694
SAM: Dude, you got issues.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.304
ELI: He's real.

04:23.219 --> 04:25.221
So, what time's your mom
picking us up?

04:25.265 --> 04:27.528
She and my dad are in
with Miss Perry.

04:27.571 --> 04:29.921
Oh, man. You can kiss
your weekends goodbye.

04:36.754 --> 04:38.887
We appreciate your concern,
Miss Perry.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.672
To be honest,
I still don't know
what the big deal is.

04:41.716 --> 04:44.675
So he told a ghost story,
and a little girl
crapped her pants?

04:46.938 --> 04:48.636
The big deal,
Mr. Braverman,

04:48.679 --> 04:52.422
is that Eli felt the need
to tell myself
and the entire class

04:52.466 --> 04:56.470
that he's being stalked
by something "evil"
in your basement.

04:56.513 --> 04:59.821
Now, these
subconscious associations

04:59.864 --> 05:02.258
are usually indicative
of a bigger problem.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.347
But there haven't been
any problems
for a long time.

05:04.391 --> 05:06.393
Hmm.

05:06.436 --> 05:07.916
Are there any
issues at home?

05:09.309 --> 05:10.353
With the marriage?

05:12.181 --> 05:15.184
Perhaps it's a result
of the change in medication.

05:18.143 --> 05:20.363
I mean no disrespect,
Mr. and Mrs. Braverman...

05:20.407 --> 05:23.671
RICHARD: Listen,
he's starting to feel
like himself again.

05:23.714 --> 05:25.281
We took him off the meds,

05:25.325 --> 05:27.718
because we don't think
he's got BPD
in the first place.

05:27.762 --> 05:31.287
I mean, these aren't
some kind of subconscious
manifestations.

05:31.331 --> 05:34.159
There's real talent here.
We should be
encouraging this.

05:34.203 --> 05:35.987
I'm not denying
his talent, Mr. Braverman,

05:36.031 --> 05:37.989
but that could
be the problem.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.949
Eli may be seeking refuge
in his imagination.

05:40.992 --> 05:43.995
It might be a good time
for a clinical reevaluation.

05:44.039 --> 05:46.215
I can set up an appointment
with the school therapist.

05:46.258 --> 05:49.087
Oh, we... You mean,
you're not accredited?

05:49.131 --> 05:50.785
RICHARD:
That won't be necessary.

05:50.828 --> 05:53.875
All right?
We'll monitor his TV,
we'll watch what he eats.

05:53.918 --> 05:55.267
Limit the sugar.
All right?

05:55.311 --> 05:56.573
This won't happen again.

05:56.617 --> 05:59.097
These kinds of drawings
cannot be taken lightly.

05:59.141 --> 06:03.232
I feel they are indicative
of one of two things.

06:03.275 --> 06:08.411
Either Eli is working
through some traumatic
childhood event,

06:08.455 --> 06:10.457
or you have a monster
living in your basement.

06:11.980 --> 06:14.417
ELI: Yeah, that's the Matrix
of Leadership.

06:14.461 --> 06:16.898
If you take that out,
he's just Hot Rod.

06:16.941 --> 06:20.510
But if you leave it in,
he becomes Rodimus Prime.

06:20.554 --> 06:21.903
-Take it out?
-No. No.

06:21.946 --> 06:23.295
We gotta keep it in.

06:23.339 --> 06:26.342
This guy is, like,
a super awesome
Transformer.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.517
Like the best
I've ever seen.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.563
He just seems boring.

06:29.606 --> 06:31.521
ELI: What do you mean?
HILLARY: Hey, guys!

06:31.565 --> 06:33.175
Hey, dude,
your girlfriend's coming.

06:33.218 --> 06:34.524
She's not my girlfriend.

06:34.568 --> 06:36.570
Fine, your stalker's coming.

06:38.876 --> 06:41.226
-Hi, Eli.
-ELI: Hey, Hillary.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.054
Eli, I believe you.

06:43.098 --> 06:45.753
I think
the Burghly Monster's
after me, too.

06:45.796 --> 06:48.973
I don't know.
How could he be after both
of us at the same time?

06:49.017 --> 06:50.322
He's a monster, Eli.

06:50.366 --> 06:51.846
He doesn't have rules.

06:51.889 --> 06:54.065
I've been hearing
strange noises
under my bed

06:54.109 --> 06:55.937
and having trouble
breathing at night.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.069
Do you keep your lights on?
He's afraid of the light.

06:58.113 --> 07:00.245
No. My mom won't let me.

07:00.289 --> 07:02.030
But I found a way
to stay safe.

07:02.073 --> 07:03.945
I recite the same prayer
every night.

07:07.035 --> 07:09.037
Now I lay me
down to sleep,

07:09.080 --> 07:11.431
I pray the Lord
my soul to keep.

07:12.388 --> 07:14.216
If I die before I wake,

07:14.259 --> 07:16.566
I pray the Lord
my soul to take.

07:16.610 --> 07:19.090
If you say that every night
before you go to bed,

07:19.134 --> 07:20.570
then nothing can get you.

07:21.876 --> 07:23.007
Thanks, Hillary.

07:31.320 --> 07:34.236
-SAM: Hi, Mr.
and Mrs. Braverman.
-Hi, Sam. Hey, bud.

07:35.106 --> 07:36.804
Hi, Mom. Hey, Dad.

07:36.847 --> 07:40.677
Hey, Sam, did you have
anything to do with this?

07:40.721 --> 07:42.940
No, Mr. Braverman.
Not this one. I swear.

07:45.377 --> 07:48.511
-Eli?
-I don't want to
talk about it.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.992
RICHARD: I thought
we were done with all
the Burghly Monster business.

07:51.688 --> 07:52.863
We are.

07:52.907 --> 07:55.300
Then why would you
curse the entire class?

07:56.998 --> 07:58.826
Mr. Braverman,
it was Emily.

07:58.869 --> 08:00.480
She tricked him
into doing it.

08:03.178 --> 08:05.049
-Eli, is that true?
-Yeah.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.314
Some of these
are worth framing.

08:09.358 --> 08:10.664
Hold onto them, okay?

08:11.491 --> 08:12.492
All right, boys,

08:13.754 --> 08:16.191
what do you say we blow
this popsicle stand?

08:17.627 --> 08:19.673
Nobody says that anymore,
Mr. Braverman.

08:23.111 --> 08:24.242
LIZ: What time is your mom
picking you up again?

08:24.286 --> 08:25.940
SAM: I think
she said around 6:00.

08:25.983 --> 08:28.551
ELI: That's not a lot of time.
We've got to get going.
Come on!

08:28.595 --> 08:29.900
We'll be in my workshop.

08:31.685 --> 08:34.731
-He seems okay to me.
-She's out of control.

08:34.775 --> 08:36.690
She's just
concerned about Eli.

08:36.733 --> 08:38.953
No.

08:38.996 --> 08:41.564
Are we afraid
to call her by name now?

08:41.608 --> 08:43.610
The only evil
possessing this house

08:43.653 --> 08:46.090
is in the form of
that 16-year-old girl.

08:46.613 --> 08:48.005
Evil?

08:48.049 --> 08:50.573
Emily is not
the only one to blame here.

08:50.617 --> 08:52.053
-You are, too.
-Me?

08:52.096 --> 08:53.968
Yes, you.
It's your dumb story.

08:54.011 --> 08:55.317
The Burghly Monster.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.449
It was a dumb story,

08:57.493 --> 08:59.147
but I didn't
tell it to him.

08:59.190 --> 09:00.844
Besides,
she's your daughter, too.

09:00.888 --> 09:02.411
Mmm.

09:02.454 --> 09:04.587
I'd like to see them
run the tests
on that one again.

09:04.631 --> 09:07.329
-EMILY: ♪ Across the Earth

09:13.596 --> 09:15.598
SAM: Dude,
this thing is killer.

09:15.642 --> 09:16.947
You never told me
you got a drone!

09:16.991 --> 09:18.035
ELI: Yeah, I just got it.

09:18.079 --> 09:19.602
Want to see
something even cooler?

09:19.646 --> 09:20.995
Set it down
on the table.

09:23.258 --> 09:24.520
Ready?

09:30.265 --> 09:32.920
Whoa!
Dude, that was awesome.

09:34.661 --> 09:38.795
This... changes... everything.

09:44.061 --> 09:46.411
♪ Shake it off
Shake it off

09:46.455 --> 09:48.675
♪ Shake it off
Shake it off ♪

10:18.835 --> 10:20.663
-You little...

10:20.707 --> 10:23.231
♪ What I'd do

10:23.274 --> 10:25.668
♪ To run with you

10:25.712 --> 10:27.539
Come back here,
you pervert!

10:38.202 --> 10:40.248
SAM: No, dude.
Left! Bottom! Go!

10:42.685 --> 10:43.686
♪ Yeah, yeah

10:43.730 --> 10:46.254
♪ Shake it off
Shake it off

10:46.297 --> 10:49.605
♪ Shake it off
Shake it off

10:49.649 --> 10:51.215
♪ I cry

10:53.740 --> 10:55.002
SAM: Awesome!

10:56.264 --> 10:57.439
Ugh!

11:04.446 --> 11:07.144
SAM: Dude, come on.
We gotta get out of here.
Quick, kill the lights.

11:11.235 --> 11:12.280
I'm coming for you.

11:14.543 --> 11:19.461
I'm gonna break
every munchkin bone

11:19.504 --> 11:22.943
in your worthless
munchkin body.

11:27.687 --> 11:28.688
I know you're in here.

12:01.938 --> 12:03.200
You're next.

12:35.842 --> 12:37.408
SAM: Dude, that was close.

12:37.452 --> 12:39.149
I can't believe
she didn't see us.

12:39.193 --> 12:41.021
She looked right at us.

12:41.064 --> 12:44.067
She's in the shower,
we got like 20 minutes.
Quick, sign in.

12:44.111 --> 12:46.374
ELI: No, you do it.
SAM: Don't be a chicken.

12:48.898 --> 12:50.160
You're a dead man.

12:50.204 --> 12:52.119
ELI: I'm already dead.

12:52.162 --> 12:54.295
Yeah, but I don't want this
on my conscience.

12:55.775 --> 12:57.689
Are you sure
it was worth it?

12:57.733 --> 12:59.822
Totally. Emily's a bitch.

12:59.866 --> 13:00.997
-Hey, look!

13:01.041 --> 13:03.434
We already got one view,
and a comment!

13:03.478 --> 13:05.654
ELI: Sweet!

13:05.697 --> 13:08.962
Are you kidding me?
She's totally
stalking you, bro.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.488
SAM: I gotta go.

13:13.531 --> 13:15.185
Wanna Facechat later?

13:15.229 --> 13:17.231
Can't. Mom's got me
on lockdown.

13:17.274 --> 13:18.754
Again?

13:18.798 --> 13:21.235
I told you how to
clear your browser.

13:21.278 --> 13:23.585
What can I say?
I like boobies.

13:23.628 --> 13:25.239
-Walkies?
-Sure.

13:27.415 --> 13:28.720
Tell your parents
I said bye.

13:29.852 --> 13:30.940
Hey, Eli!

13:35.423 --> 13:36.641
Peace out.

14:05.670 --> 14:06.758
Just like new.

14:09.152 --> 14:10.893
LIZ: Eli! Time for dinner.

14:10.937 --> 14:12.068
Coming!

14:18.466 --> 14:20.120
LIZ: You're gonna screw up
your calorie count.

14:20.163 --> 14:22.774
RICHARD: Fifty sit-ups,
and it'll be like
it never happened.

14:24.037 --> 14:25.299
LIZ: Eli, can you
turn that off, please?

14:26.126 --> 14:27.910
RICHARD: Yeah, buddy.

14:27.954 --> 14:30.043
You gotta come back
to the real world from
time to time. Come on.

14:30.086 --> 14:31.522
ELI: If you say so.

14:31.566 --> 14:33.481
EMILY: You are an animal!

14:33.524 --> 14:35.700
A disgusting little pig!

14:35.744 --> 14:37.441
-RICHARD: Hey!
-Look what he did!

14:38.486 --> 14:39.574
He's a little pervert.

14:39.617 --> 14:41.097
He put this on the web!

14:41.141 --> 14:42.272
All of my friends
are going to see it.

14:42.316 --> 14:43.839
I'm gonna have to
be home-schooled.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.015
RICHARD: Okay,
relax with the drama.
Let me see.

14:51.325 --> 14:53.980
I... There's only
five hits on this.

14:54.023 --> 14:56.939
He tagged it,
"Sister Gone Wild."

14:56.983 --> 14:59.594
If that goes viral,
the whole world
is going to see it.

14:59.637 --> 15:02.553
-Oh, God!
-Take it down!

15:08.429 --> 15:09.821
-Mom!
-Enough.

15:10.997 --> 15:12.737
All right, Eli,
take it down.

15:20.310 --> 15:23.400
-There. It's gone.

15:23.444 --> 15:26.751
No computers, no video games,
nothing digital for a month.

15:26.795 --> 15:28.492
That's not fair!

15:28.536 --> 15:30.842
Don't look at me, bud.
I can't help you out
with this one.

15:30.886 --> 15:34.716
That's it? A few weeks
without video games?
Are you kidding me?

15:36.500 --> 15:38.720
Don't let them fool you.

15:39.939 --> 15:43.333
You're not normal.

15:43.377 --> 15:44.856
RICHARD AND LIZ: Emily!

15:44.900 --> 15:45.988
You never will be.

15:46.032 --> 15:47.033
Emily!

15:47.076 --> 15:49.426
Look at me. Get upstairs.

15:50.079 --> 15:51.602
Truth hurts.

15:51.646 --> 15:54.692
Yeah, it's gonna hurt worse.
Get upstairs. This is mine.

15:58.870 --> 16:00.307
Christ.

16:00.350 --> 16:02.135
You all right, big guy?

16:02.178 --> 16:03.484
You know she didn't mean it.

16:03.527 --> 16:04.528
Yes, she did.

16:04.572 --> 16:06.661
No, she didn't. She's...

16:07.401 --> 16:08.968
She's just being Emily.

16:09.011 --> 16:10.970
You know you can't
antagonize her like that.

16:11.013 --> 16:15.365
But she tricked me into
telling the whole class
about the Burghly Monster.

16:22.155 --> 16:23.808
-RICHARD: You know what?
-What?

16:25.723 --> 16:28.639
You're right.
This is a really
scary basement.

16:29.901 --> 16:31.381
Maybe I should finish it.

16:33.079 --> 16:35.298
Reminds me of
the basement I grew up in
when I was a kid.

16:36.082 --> 16:37.953
-And guess what.
-What?

16:37.997 --> 16:40.912
I thought the Burghly Monster
lived in my basement, too.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.004
I know. Emily told me.

16:45.047 --> 16:46.483
And now he's after me.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.311
Emily said that
just to scare you.

16:48.355 --> 16:50.096
Like your Uncle Kevin
and Uncle Gary.

16:50.139 --> 16:51.923
They made him up
to scare me.

16:51.967 --> 16:54.622
I don't even know
where they came up
with that stupid name.

16:54.665 --> 16:58.756
Dad, the Burghly Monster
did come after you.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.498
No, he didn't, buddy.
I'm sorry.

17:01.542 --> 17:04.675
That was a story I told Emily
just to get her to behave.

17:06.329 --> 17:07.417
It's not real.

17:07.461 --> 17:10.072
He's real. I can feel him.

17:10.116 --> 17:12.640
When I turn off the lights,
it's like I've opened
a door for him.

17:12.683 --> 17:14.294
Calm down.

17:14.337 --> 17:16.209
Okay? Take a deep breath.

17:20.778 --> 17:21.823
All right.

17:21.866 --> 17:23.259
Do you really think
there's anything

17:23.303 --> 17:25.566
that I wouldn't do
to protect you?

17:25.609 --> 17:28.569
I will turn on
every light in this house.

17:28.612 --> 17:31.876
I will go put giant floodlights
out in the front lawn,

17:31.920 --> 17:33.835
and I'll point them
in every direction.

17:33.878 --> 17:34.879
But you know what?

17:35.924 --> 17:37.926
That's not going
to stop the fear.

17:40.146 --> 17:44.846
So, let's say that there is
a Burghly Monster, big deal.

17:44.889 --> 17:48.937
The only thing you need to
be concerned with is the light
you have inside you.

17:48.980 --> 17:50.199
Right here.

17:54.464 --> 17:56.640
Wow. Your light is strong.

17:58.729 --> 17:59.948
How do you know?

18:01.210 --> 18:02.516
'Cause I'm your dad.

18:04.779 --> 18:06.520
Does everyone
have this light?

18:07.086 --> 18:08.130
Yeah.

18:08.174 --> 18:09.436
Even Emily?

18:09.479 --> 18:13.135
Yeah, hers just isn't
that bright right now.

18:13.179 --> 18:16.095
I'll tell you what,
we're going to test
this out. Okay?

18:16.138 --> 18:19.837
I want you to stay right here,
and we are going
to count to 10.

18:19.881 --> 18:21.100
No, Dad.

18:21.143 --> 18:24.015
-Yes, it's just 10 seconds.
- No.

18:24.059 --> 18:26.235
Okay? I'm going to be
at the top of the stairs,
waiting.

18:27.018 --> 18:28.063
Okay?

18:29.195 --> 18:30.413
Okay.

18:30.457 --> 18:31.501
You can do this.

18:36.680 --> 18:38.769
Remember, buddy,
you're a Braverman.

18:41.642 --> 18:43.078
ELI: One...

18:47.213 --> 18:48.388
two...

18:59.050 --> 19:00.051
three...

19:13.239 --> 19:14.457
four...

19:16.807 --> 19:18.200
five...

19:22.248 --> 19:23.553
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

20:35.234 --> 20:36.278
What's going on, buddy?

20:36.322 --> 20:38.802
Can I watch TV
with you guys?

20:38.846 --> 20:42.676
I'm sorry. I won't even watch,
I'll just sit in the room.

20:42.719 --> 20:44.112
You know, to be fair,

20:44.155 --> 20:46.723
the sentence should
officially commence tomorrow,

20:46.767 --> 20:49.248
seeing that it happened
so late in the day today.

20:50.118 --> 20:51.380
Who are you, his attorney?

20:52.076 --> 20:53.164
Please?

20:53.208 --> 20:55.819
No talking. No snacks.
Bed by 11:00.

20:57.343 --> 20:58.387
Deal.

21:08.963 --> 21:12.445
LIZ: Only one kernel.

21:12.488 --> 21:14.098
WEATHERMAN ON TV:
Seventy-two degrees
was the high today.

21:14.142 --> 21:16.057
That's about average
for this time of year.

21:16.100 --> 21:18.102
Now, as we look
to our satellite,

21:18.146 --> 21:21.497
you can see we're in
for some late night storm
activity tomorrow night.

21:21.541 --> 21:23.282
For all you sky watchers
out there,

21:23.325 --> 21:27.329
NASA's warning of
some light solar flare
