25:32.531 --> 25:33.619
You're okay.

25:37.492 --> 25:40.495
Are you purposely trying
to scar him for life?

25:40.539 --> 25:42.584
That was
borderline psychotic.

25:42.628 --> 25:44.281
So was what he did to me.

25:44.325 --> 25:47.154
I feel violated.
Then to see that
posted online.

25:47.197 --> 25:49.069
Oh, stop. It was
an innocent prank.

25:49.939 --> 25:51.550
It wasn't that innocent.

25:53.377 --> 25:55.641
I agree. He had no right
to record you,

25:55.684 --> 25:58.121
but he's
your little brother.

25:58.165 --> 26:00.428
You know how much he's
been through this past year.

26:05.215 --> 26:08.741
You're right.
I went too far.

26:08.784 --> 26:10.786
I'll take him out
for ice cream
and apologize.

26:12.309 --> 26:13.397
That would be nice.

26:14.398 --> 26:16.183
Just do me a favor.

26:16.226 --> 26:19.186
When you're done,
leave the lights on.

27:03.056 --> 27:05.188
Facebook's up $10.

27:05.232 --> 27:06.625
I should have bought in
when you told me to.

27:09.323 --> 27:11.978
-What is that?
-What?

27:12.500 --> 27:13.501
That.

27:14.458 --> 27:15.895
Hand over the iPad.

27:17.679 --> 27:19.725
When you're
done with breakfast,
go grab the rest.

27:21.901 --> 27:24.555
Hi, Mrs. Braverman.
Can Eli come out and play?

27:24.599 --> 27:27.036
Sam! How did you get here?

27:27.733 --> 27:29.386
SAM: I rode my bike.

27:29.430 --> 27:31.301
That's a really long ride.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.564
Eh. It wasn't too bad.

27:33.608 --> 27:35.044
Does your mom
know you're here?

27:35.088 --> 27:36.655
She's still sleeping.

27:36.698 --> 27:38.613
She had a late
work night last night.

27:38.657 --> 27:40.397
Ah. Okay.

27:40.441 --> 27:42.486
Well, we'll call her
in a little bit,
let her know you're here.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.054
Eli, guess who's here.

27:45.359 --> 27:46.360
Sam!

27:47.840 --> 27:50.233
Sam. You'll never believe
what happened.

27:50.277 --> 27:52.801
Hold up, everyone.
You are supposed
to be grounded.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.107
Come on, Mom.

27:56.936 --> 27:58.415
Have you eaten
anything yet?

27:58.459 --> 27:59.460
Uh, a little.

28:00.113 --> 28:01.897
Kitchen. You, shower.

28:02.637 --> 28:03.899
ELI: Come on.

28:03.943 --> 28:06.119
I found this video on how
to make ectoplasm.

28:06.162 --> 28:07.250
Great.

28:38.368 --> 28:40.370
Hey, at least
clear my browser.

28:43.634 --> 28:44.635
Oh.

28:45.462 --> 28:47.682
Oh, no.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.902
She knows where you live.

28:50.816 --> 28:52.426
She's not that bad.

28:52.469 --> 28:53.514
What?

28:55.516 --> 28:57.692
-Hey, Hillary.
-HILLARY: Eli, are you okay?

28:57.736 --> 28:59.128
ELI: Yeah.

28:59.172 --> 29:01.565
I think the Burghly Monster
came for me last night.

29:01.609 --> 29:04.960
Hillary, you can't just
pretend to see something
just to be my friend.

29:05.004 --> 29:07.615
I'm not pretending.
I have proof.

29:08.572 --> 29:10.183
Here, read these.

29:10.226 --> 29:12.794
I think the Burghly Monster
was a real man.

29:12.838 --> 29:18.104
"A lumber baron heir,
R.L. Burghly was arrested
late last night

29:18.147 --> 29:20.106
"after mounds
of charred limbs

29:20.149 --> 29:22.673
"were discovered
in the furnace
of Burghly Lumber."

29:24.023 --> 29:25.372
Read the next one.

29:27.766 --> 29:30.420
"The charred body
of R.L. Burghly

29:30.464 --> 29:32.901
"was found in his cell
New Year's Day.

29:32.945 --> 29:35.730
"The prison guards
could not identify
the source of the fire."

29:37.558 --> 29:41.214
SAM:
Analysis complete.
You're both crazy.

29:41.257 --> 29:43.912
Sam, you gotta listen.
This is serious.

29:43.956 --> 29:46.523
Burghly Lumber
used to be here
in West Bloomfield.

29:46.567 --> 29:48.830
It was turned into
a huge nursery.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.789
I think that's where
it all started.

29:52.834 --> 29:56.707
I gotta go.
My mom's waiting. Bye.

29:58.144 --> 30:00.233
SAM: Man, and I thought
you had issues.

30:02.322 --> 30:04.498
ELI: We've gotta
go check this out.

30:04.541 --> 30:06.152
I thought he lived
in your basement?

30:06.195 --> 30:08.284
Sam, this could
be a source.

30:08.328 --> 30:10.896
A source of what?

30:19.252 --> 30:21.341
SAM: You know
this is crazy, right?

30:21.384 --> 30:23.256
Emily's behind all of it.

30:23.299 --> 30:26.346
ELI: I'm not crazy.
There's something
to this.

30:26.389 --> 30:28.391
SAM: Can't you just
tell your mom and dad?

30:28.435 --> 30:30.089
They'll put an end
to all of this.

30:30.132 --> 30:31.612
ELI: No. They won't.

30:31.655 --> 30:34.093
They'll just put me
back on those pills again.

30:34.136 --> 30:35.834
SAM: That might not
be a bad idea.

30:39.794 --> 30:41.752
Do you even know
what you're looking for?

30:41.796 --> 30:43.145
ELI: I'll know it
when I see it.

30:44.843 --> 30:46.105
ELI: Hey, wait up.

30:46.148 --> 30:47.497
SAM: Dude, check this out!

30:47.541 --> 30:48.847
-What's up, goat?

30:50.587 --> 30:53.242
-Don't hurt me
-MAN: I'm gonna go
check on the goats.

30:53.286 --> 30:57.116
Hey, you boys interested
in some goat's milk?

30:57.159 --> 30:58.247
No, sir.

30:58.291 --> 31:00.641
Well, then the nursery's
down that way.

31:00.684 --> 31:03.296
Hey, mister, you ever hear
of Burghly Lumber?

31:07.474 --> 31:09.302
MAN: Burghly Lumber?

31:09.345 --> 31:13.175
Be careful, kids.
We don't use that name
around here anymore.

31:16.135 --> 31:18.180
As the story goes,

31:18.224 --> 31:21.183
that old man Burghly
killed the kids here.

31:23.316 --> 31:27.146
Didn't happen here.
He liked to run the saws.

31:27.189 --> 31:31.541
Chopped the kids into pieces,
like chicken.

31:33.021 --> 31:35.023
Then he'd bring
what was left back here,

31:35.067 --> 31:36.938
got rid of the evidence.

31:36.982 --> 31:40.072
Twelve kids later,
there was nothing.

31:40.115 --> 31:43.553
No skin, no bones,
not even a tooth.

31:44.685 --> 31:46.556
It was like
they all disappeared.

31:49.385 --> 31:52.606
When I was a kid,
around you boys' age,

31:52.649 --> 31:55.130
one of my friends
come up missing.

31:55.174 --> 31:57.524
He came to the furnace
and climbed in,

31:58.177 --> 32:00.570
and he never came out.

32:00.614 --> 32:02.833
So, he died
in the furnace?

32:02.877 --> 32:04.226
Wanna poke your head in
and see?

32:08.404 --> 32:10.580
Here, let's see if
you can wake him up.

32:13.322 --> 32:16.586
Throw it in.
You won't even hear a sound.

32:31.732 --> 32:33.690
Huh, guess he's not home.

32:42.482 --> 32:44.571
SAM: Come on.
Don't be chicken.

32:44.614 --> 32:45.876
ELI: I'm not a chicken.

32:45.920 --> 32:48.662
That guy just
freaked me out a little.

32:48.705 --> 32:51.230
SAM: Yeah. He's just old.

32:52.057 --> 32:54.407
Besides, I'm with you.

33:06.810 --> 33:09.378
Stop. I've seen this movie.

33:09.422 --> 33:10.771
It's just going to explode.

33:11.815 --> 33:12.991
Come on.

33:16.124 --> 33:18.779
Man. You got a lot
of junk down here.

33:20.694 --> 33:23.175
What is this?

33:23.218 --> 33:25.351
It's a family relic.
Be careful.

33:29.224 --> 33:32.010
So, this is where
the big BM lives.

33:34.534 --> 33:38.016
No. He lives over there,
by the furnace.

33:51.594 --> 33:52.856
I wanna meet him.

34:00.038 --> 34:03.998
It's practically summer.
Why's your furnace
even running?

34:04.042 --> 34:05.478
ELI: It's always running.

34:10.222 --> 34:12.702
This thing is like
100 years old.

34:14.313 --> 34:16.315
Sam, look.

34:22.843 --> 34:24.714
That's impossible.

34:57.182 --> 34:58.661
Anyone home?

35:26.559 --> 35:27.995
Sam, let's get out of here.

35:31.825 --> 35:33.000
